namedLocations.description: A resel is a resolution element - a concept used in image analysis. It describes the actual spatial image resolution in an image. The number of resels in the image will be lower or equal to the number of pixel/voxels in the image. In an actual image the resels can vary across the image and indeed the local resolution can be expressed as "resels per pixel". In functional neuroimaging analysis, an estimate of the number of resels together with random field theory is used in statistical inference. Keith Worsley has proposed an estimate for the number of resels/roughness. The word "resel" is related to the words "pixel" and "voxel", and Waldo R. Tobler is probably among the first to use the word.

transcript.text: Hello everyone I will just give you a quick overview of Visual Approval tool which is a specially designed add on module which is available to all our customers.

And the objective of visual approval tool is to simplify the communication with your end customers especially for the artwork approval And normally in order processing, the majority time goes in artwork approval where you have to send them a file and you need to get an approval from the customer and customer also requires some changes on the file prepared by you.
But they need to give you the comments so they have to write you an e-mail.
So that is a long communication and lot of time is going in terms of managing the artwork approval history.
So let me show you how the tool works.
Now when you receive an order, there could be case where customer have uploaded the file but there are some errors in the file.
So you have to revise the file and maybe send them an approval or they hire your designing services.
You are designing the file for them but when the file is ready you need to send to them for an approval.
So that case is the visual proofing tool is very very useful.
So here this is the order number 333 which has four items and one item.
I am just uploading a file and I am asking customer to approve.
So here I can upload the file.
The file could be single page, multi page and I can ask for an approval and I can use this visual proof and I can say file is ready kindly approve.
So what this will do?
This will trigger an e-mail to the customer.
Customer will get an e-mail that you have uploaded a file and you need to approve.
So here it says the proof is available.
Now this is an inbox of the customer and it shows me basically the e-mail from you that the proof is available.
Go and see the proof.
You can also personalize the e-mail which is being sent from the system.
And here I am logging as a customer account and it shows me that one of the file requires a proof approval.
So here if I click on review your proof, the visual interface will open up.
The visual interface would allow users to see multiple pages onto the file and then on any particular section if they want to give you an input they can easily give the input.
So there are some specialized tools like annotation, highlights, pointer.
All this is given to the customer to give you notes.
So here I am saying that OK this particular section make it bigger and this particular section for example highlight more font has to be changed.

So this is an end customer giving you an input and here I can say make changes and send new proof or I can also say that the file is fine so I can approve but I'm saying that I need to have the changes before you print the file.
Now this there could be multiple cases where all these inputs are coming to you and you are reworking on the file.
For example, customer have given you the comments and then your graphic design is reworking on the file and then you are again sending the file back to the customer for an approve.

So this is like one of the sample file which customer have given an input and then you send them a file back and says all changes are done and approve but another cycle came where customer given you another inputs.
So what we are doing is whatever communication is done at each approval cycle everything is stored.
So whatever customer is giving you a feedback from the tool and whatever comments you are sending to the customer, it is recorded into an order history.

So here if you see in the back end, this is recorded here for the printer and graphic designer to see the comments which are given by customer and it is also recorded at the My account section at the customer's end.
So whatever communication is done, it is also recorded here.
So here also he is able to see basically whatever approval cycle and the proof feedback which is given by them to you and whatever comments you are placing to them.
So this makes a particular communication very transparent and clear and they always have access to the notes which they have given to you and you also have all the communication at your end.
Thanks a lot for watching this video.
If you need any more information on this tool or if you need personalized demo, you can always contact us from onpinshop.com or also e-mail us at sales@onpinshop.com.
Thank you.
Bye bye.
